  <cateringDescription><![CDATA[<p>The panoramic restaurant overlooks the gardens and is a great spot for a hearty breakfast before a day of exploring. Breakfast is amazing and includes hot options like bacon, local sausages and eggs. Freshly brewed coffees, teas and delicious fruit juices are also available. It even has a prosecco bar, a fresh orange juice machine and slabs of fresh honeycomb!</p>
<p>If you upgrade to half board you'll have dinner at the five-star sister hotel <a data-udi="umb://document/8d7a83200b954c858bcfb2007c1d6644" href="/{localLink:umb://document/8d7a83200b954c858bcfb2007c1d6644}" title="Park Hotel Mignon">Park Hotel Mignon</a>, just a 10-minute stroll down the road. It's a wonderful culinary experience with a five-course menu; the desserts are also delicious so make sure you leave some room! </p>
<p>A small bar serves a fantastic selection of local and specialist wines as well as popular Italian cocktails.</p>
<p><em>The Park Hotel Mignon requests a smart dress code at dinner, with no shorts, sportswear, or flip-flops to be worn. </em></p>]]></cateringDescription>
