  <description><![CDATA[<p>Hotel Adria brings an Art Nouveau building into a new era with its perfect blend of classic interiors and modern comforts. Think parquet floors, and vintage furniture. The attention to detail is incredible and it’s instantly a place where you feel at home.</p>
<h2>Wonderful spa facilities</h2>
<p>We love heading straight for the spa when we arrive here. There’s a modern indoor pool with hydro-massage fountains, Turkish bath, hot tub, salt steam bath and whirlpool. The spa area has views of the gardens that surround the hotel. The Mediterranean sauna is amazing and has the most peaceful, calming atmosphere. We could spend all day switching from spa room to spa room.</p>
<h2>Best breakfast in Merano</h2>
<p>Food's an incredibly important part of Italian culture and the Adria embraces that whole-heartedly. The breakfast here is out of this world, with slabs of honey comb and bottles of prosecco, they really spoil you! Expect home-made pastries for breakfast and if you upgrade to half board you'll have gourmet five course dinners at the five-star sister hotel <a data-udi="umb://document/8d7a83200b954c858bcfb2007c1d6644" href="/{localLink:umb://document/8d7a83200b954c858bcfb2007c1d6644}" title="Park Hotel Mignon">Park Hotel Mignon</a>, just down the road.</p>
<h2>Great for walkers</h2>
<p>If you’d rather get straight out and explore the town, the centre's just a 15-minute downhill walk away. You'll definitely get your steps in walking back up to the hotel after your day in town! The hotel's ideal for keen walkers and ideal if you're looking for a combination of exploring on foot and discovering the local culture.</p>]]></description>
